<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10520685>
    dc:description "Fig. 3 a-i (graphic scale, μm). Magnolioxylon kräuselii (Greguss) Van der Burgh, 1973, Ociu, Bisericii brook, South Apuseni, Romania, sample OB-1. a-c. (cross section) – distinct boundary of growth ring, marked by marginal parenchyma and ray dilations; d-f. (tangential section) – spiral thickenings and scalariform pitting on vessels, biseriate heterogeneous rays; g-i. Radial section – spiral thickenings and scalariform pitting on vessels, scalariform perforation plates, pitted cross-fields." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10520685/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

